Reasoning: The paper deals with the classification of perfect binary one-error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The classification relies on the recent classification of Steiner quadruple systems, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The efficient generation of codes also involves combinatorial algorithms and data structures, which fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also mentions the classification of optimal binary one-error-correcting codes of length 14 and (15, 1024, 4) codes, which are topics in cryptography (cs.CR).
